\N<Segi>Mm... Ah.

\N<Segi>What do you mean...?

Isn't that right?
3_セギ11a
\N<Segi>...

\N<Fubii>Ahaha, it's obvious when you see them. Right? It's
frustrating, isn't it?

\N<Fubii>If it were me, I wouldn't be so hesitant. If I like someone,
I'd just say it and embrace them, that's all.

\N<Segi>That's... up to the person involved... Don't assume everyone
is like you...

\N<Fubii>But seriously? You'd be troubled if I became Rame's
boyfriend, wouldn't you? Auntie, you'd be jealous of her,
right?
\N<Segi>Don't talk nonsense... There's no way that's true!

\N<Fubii>Ahaha, really? I wouldn't like it if auntie got obsessed
with another man besides me.

\N<Fubii>For example... like staying overnight at the house of a dull

\N<Segi>...!

\N<Fubii>What's wrong? Does that strike a nerve? Surely not, right?
You wouldn't do such a thing, especially with a son, right?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Fubii>Well, I can understand the uncle's feelings though. After
all, you want to spend as much time as possible with the
person you like, don't you?
\N<Segi>What are you... trying to say...?

\N<Fubii>No, what I'm saying is... I like you, auntie. And you're not
entirely against it. So there's only one thing to do here,
right?

\N<Segi>Wh-What are you talking about...? We can't possibly do that
here...!

\N<Segi>Ah... mmm... ha... ah!

\N<Fubii>About what we were talking about earlier, is it true that
Riia really likes that girl?

\N<Segi>Mm... ha...! E-Even if that's the case... it's a matter for
them to discuss...!

\N<Segi>You and... I-I, as outsiders, shouldn't be... mmm! Stirring
things up... ah...!
\N<Fubii>Eh? You're not an outsider. You're his mother, after all.

\N<Segi>Even so...! Until those kids and Rame can properly express
their feelings... it's not for others to interfere...!

\N<Segi>Is that clear? Even knowing that...! What you're doing is...
mmm! Can't you realize it's the worst kind of behavior...?

\N<Fubii>Is that so? I don't really understand what you're saying,
auntie.

\N<Fubii>But... your son is such a fool. If the conditions are right,
women will fall for a forceful man... right? You're the
same, aren't you, auntie?
\N<Segi>That can't be true... What are you talking about...?

\N<Fubii>Really? But here you are accepting me. Well, that's also
because I have a special fondness for you.
\N<Segi>What did you say...?

\N<Fubii>Because your body feels good. On the other hand, Rame's body
is so meager that I'm not really interested.

\N<Fubii>Well, there might be someone who likes her for what she is.
Maybe she has potential for the future?

\N<Fubii>So that's why... I think it was good that I chose you as my
lover.
\N<Segi>L-Lover...? What are you talking about...?
\N<Fubii>Because you're going to replace Rame for me, right?

\N<Fubii>I was supposed to become lovers with her. But you said
that's not allowed. So isn't it natural for you to become my
lover instead?

\N<Segi>Enough with the jokes...! There's no way you and I could
become lovers...

\N<Fubii>Ah, because of the age difference? Do you care about that
too, auntie?
\N<Segi>That's not what I'm talking about...!

\N<Fubii>Besides... Look. Despite how much you resisted, isn't the
fact that you're doing this here with me proof enough of our
relationship as lovers...?
\N<Segi>They're nowhere to be seen... but...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Segi>Why on earth are the two of them doing this...
